<subSubSection id="C31C65001972FFB36A8BA59B7115FCDB" lastPageId="84" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1972FFB56A8BA59B7162F982" blockId="82.[189,334,1532,1558]" box="[189,334,1532,1558]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<heading id="D0F181E71972FFB56A8BA59B7162F982" bold="true" box="[189,334,1532,1558]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA991972FFB56A8BA59B7162F982" bold="true" box="[189,334,1532,1558]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1972FFB56ADCA64D7106F9D0" blockId="82.[189,630,1578,1640]" box="[234,298,1578,1604]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="B972EA991972FFB56ADCA64D7106F9D0" bold="true" box="[234,298,1578,1604]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1972FFB56A8BA629725AF9FC" blockId="82.[189,630,1578,1640]" box="[189,630,1614,1640]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
LENGTH. Body 
<quantity id="4CFE9B6E1972FFB56B5CA62971EBF9FC" box="[362,455,1614,1640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
, wing 
<quantity id="4CFE9B6E1972FFB56822A629725DF9FC" box="[532,625,1614,1640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1972FFB56A8BA6F77181F87D" blockId="82.[189,1399,1680,2025]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
HEAD. Face in lateral view concave, weakly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence very weakly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 6.0; ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 1.5; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 2.3. Face black, light grey pollinose, long pilose along eye-margin. Hypostomal bridge yellow, long pale pilose. Gena and mouth edge yellow with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons and vertex black, slightly pollinose, a squarish area posterior of lunula non-pollinose and shiny (
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1972FFB569A4A72673D1F8CF" box="[914,1021,1857,1883]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="86.[189,232,1787,1813]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,412,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@86.[189,1399,412,1739]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="Fig. 38. Head, lateral view (C, K), dorsal view (A–B, D, F–J, L) and frontal view (E). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) farinosa sp. nov.,holotype, Ƌ, Sabah, Malaysia. B. S. (A.) fimbriata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Thailand. C–D. S. (A.) forceps Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. E. S. (A.) furva Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. F. S. (A.) ghatsi, sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. G. S. (A.) gigantea sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. H. S. (A.) granditarsis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Thailand. I. S. (A.) hamulata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. J. S. (A.) hansoni Thompson, 1966, holotype, Ƌ, Nepal. K–L. S. (A.) hauseri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Nepal. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830632/files/figure.png" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Fig. 38F</figureCitation>
); pile short, light yellow. Frons with clear but narrow furrow medially. Occiput black, light grey pollinose, light yellow pilose. Eye with an area of enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna brown-yellow with black setae dorsally on scape and pedicel; basoflagellomere oval, ratio width: length 1: 1.3; arista short pilose, about 3 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1973FFB46A8BA16D7237FE24" blockId="83.[189,1399,266,432]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">THORAX. Colour black, postpronotum, postalar callus and dorso-medial part of anepisternum and anepimeron yellow; greyish pollinose, posterior margin of katepisternum narrowly non-pollinose, shiny; scutum and pleuron with very short adpressed light yellow pile. Scutellum semi-lunular shaped, black, weakly pollinose, with pile slightly longer than on scutum, without observable setae at posterior margin, unclear if they are broken off.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7966031973FFB46A8BA7ED7142F87E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830628" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3830628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830628/files/figure.png" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" startId="83.[189,232,1930,1956]" targetBox="[200,1373,517,1891]" targetPageId="83">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1973FFB46A8BA7ED7142F87E" blockId="83.[189,1399,1930,2026]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB46A8BA7ED7130F830" bold="true" box="[189,284,1930,1956]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Fig. 36.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081973FFB46B10A7ED728EF830" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[294,674,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghatsi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB46B10A7ED728EF830" box="[294,674,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E21973FFB4689AA7ED7320F830" box="[684,780,1930,1956]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, 
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB469A5A7EC7385F831" bold="true" box="[915,937,1931,1957]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">♂</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB4698CA7ED73E3F830" bold="true" box="[954,975,1930,1956]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">A</emphasis>
. Sternum IV, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB46F16A7ED7518F830" bold="true" box="[1312,1332,1930,1956]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">B</emphasis>
. Left surstylus, lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB46BE7A7CA71CAF853" bold="true" box="[465,486,1965,1991]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">C</emphasis>
. Left superior lobe, lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991973FFB4694FA7CA73A2F853" bold="true" box="[889,910,1965,1991]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">D</emphasis>
. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36A8BA16D7195FED3" blockId="84.[189,1399,266,327]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">WING. Entirely microtrichose; hyaline, stigma yellowish. Crossvein dm-cu meeting vein M slightly obliquely and vein M</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36B8FA12771EEFEDA" box="[441,450,320,334]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">1</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36BFFA14A7250FED3" blockId="84.[189,1399,266,327]" box="[457,636,301,327]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">meeting vein R</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB3684AA12772BBFEDA" box="[636,663,320,334]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">4+5</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB368A8A14A7370FED3" blockId="84.[189,1399,266,327]" box="[670,860,301,327]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">perpendicularly.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36A8BA1087186FE60" blockId="84.[189,1399,367,500]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
LEGS. Pro- and mesoleg yellow, tarsomeres 4 and 5 black. Metaleg, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1974FFB369FCA108741CFE1D" box="[970,1072,367,393]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="78.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,785,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[189,1399,785,1777]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Fig. 33. Metaleg, anterior view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) crassispina Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, ♀, Myanmar. B. S. (A.) crucivena Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. C. S. (A.) exilipes sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Java. D. S. (A.) forficata Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. E. S. (A.) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. F. S. (A.) gigantea sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. G. S. (A.) gigas Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, ♀, Myanmar. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830617/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 33E</figureCitation>
, with coxa black, trochanter yellow; femur black with basal 
<emphasis id="B972EA991974FFB36807A1F4726BFE39" bold="true" box="[561,583,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">⅓</emphasis>
yellow, strongly incrassate, ratio width: length 1: 3.0; tibia black and yellow biannulate with long and wide apicoventral dens; tarsus entirely black, basitarsomere thick, ratio width: length 1: 3.2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36A8BA27B7146FD7D" blockId="84.[189,1399,540,745]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 3.2: 2.0: 1.8; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 2.7 and 1: 0.7. Terga black, anterior 2/5 of tergum III with yellow fascia; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with a more or less horizontal row of 3–4 light yellow setae at lateral margin; sternum III without sclerotized part; sternum IV, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1974FFB36EB2A2EF74DEFD36" box="[1156,1266,648,674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[200,1373,517,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[189,1399,511,1895]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 36. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830628/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 36A</figureCitation>
; sterna VI, VII and VIII simple, with long yellow pile. Genitalia, 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1974FFB3697DA2CC738CFD51" box="[843,928,683,709]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="83.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[200,1373,517,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[189,1399,511,1895]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Fig. 36. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) ghatsi sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830628/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
B–D: note the symmetrical surstyli and superior lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB36ADCA3767169FCBF" blockId="84.[189,325,785,847]" box="[234,325,785,811]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="B972EA991974FFB36ADCA3767169FCBF" bold="true" box="[234,325,785,811]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
